hu.elte.txtuml.api

Interface ModelElement

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    BlockBody, Condition, ModelValue, ParameterizedBlockBody<T>, ParameterizedCondition<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Action, Association, Event, Model, ModelBool, ModelBool.Else, ModelClass, ModelExecutor, ModelExecutor.Settings, ModelInt, ModelString, ModelType, Region, Signal, StateMachine, StateMachine.Choice, StateMachine.CompositeState, StateMachine.Initial, StateMachine.Pseudostate, StateMachine.State, StateMachine.Transition, StateMachine.Vertex

    public interface ModelElement
    Base interface for elements of the model.

    Represents: subtypes represent elements of the model

    Usage:

    Should not be used directly.

    Java restrictions:

    • Define subtype: disallowed

    See the documentation of Model for an overview on modeling in txtUML.

    Implementation note:

    It is needed for AspectJ to work well. All types that are used in the model should implement this interface (not directly but through inheritance).

    Author:
    Gabor Ferenc Kovacs
